OL,5,CEdwards case
OL,7,FThe boss of the BBC Tim Davie will be
OL,8,Fquestioned by the Culture Secretary
OL,9,FLisa Nandy over the broadcaster's
OL,10,Fhandling of the Huw Edwards case.
OL,12,FThe veteran broadcaster, who was the
OL,13,FBBC's highest-paid newsreader before
OL,14,Fhe resigned in April, admitted on
OL,15,FWednesday to making indecent images of
OL,16,Fchildren.
