OL,7,FThe BBC has said it knew of the
OL,8,Fveteran broadcaster's arrest on
OL,9,F"suspicion of serious offences" in
OL,10,FNovember, but continued employing him
OL,11,Funtil April.
OL,13,FCulture Secretary Lisa Nandy is
OL,14,Fexpected to hold urgent talks with the
OL,15,FBBC's Director General Tim Davie on
OL,16,FThursday, according to BBC News.
OL,18,FThe broadcaster paid Huw Edwards
OL,19,Fbetween #475,000 and #479,999 for the
OL,20,Fyear 2023/24.
