OL,7,F"If at any point during the period Mr
OL,8,FEdwards was employed by the BBC he had
OL,9,Fbeen charged, the BBC had determined
OL,10,Fit would act immediately to dismiss
OL,11,Fhim. In the end, at the point of
OL,12,Fcharge he was no longer an employee of
OL,13,Fthe BBC.
OL,15,F"During this period, in the usual way,
OL,16,Fthe BBC has kept its corporate
OL,17,Fmanagement of these issues separate
OL,18,Ffrom its independent editorial
OL,19,Ffunctions."
